### If Search Fails

```
❌ Green dot but search failed. Let me check the logs...
```

Then run:

```bash
# Find the most recent Cursor MCP log
LOG_FILE=$(find ~/Library/Application\ Support/Cursor/logs -name "*mcp*.log" -type f 2>/dev/null | xargs -I {} stat -f "%m %N" {} 2>/dev/null | sort -rn | head -1 | cut -d' ' -f2-)

if [ -n "$LOG_FILE" ]; then
  echo "📋 Most recent MCP log:"
  echo ""
  echo "Last 30 lines:"
  tail -30 "$LOG_FILE" | grep -i vault
else
  echo "❌ No MCP logs found"
